  43,34,and (silver) doors for their houses and (silver) couches that they lean on it
  43,35,and (gold) ornament. And all that is only an enjoyment of this worldâ€™s life while the hereafter with your Master is for those who control themselves
  43,36,"And anyone who is blind about remembrance of the beneficent, We appoint a devil to him to be close to him"
  43,37,"and indeed they shall obstruct them from the (right) way, and they think they are guided"
  43,38,"Until when he comes to Us, saying: I wish there was distance of the two easts (the east and the west) between you (the appointed devil) and me, what a bad companion"
  43,39,"And (you regret) never benefits you today, since you did wrong, indeed you are partners in the punishment"
  43,40,"Can you make the deaf hear, or guide the blind and anyone who is in an obvious error"
  43,41,"So if We take you away (from this world), then indeed We take revenge from them"
  43,42,"Or (if) We show you that which We promised them, then We indeed have power over them (to do that)"
  43,43,"So hold on to that which We revealed to you, indeed you are on a straight path"
  43,44,"And indeed it (Quran) is a reminder for you and for your people, and you will be questioned"
  43,45,"And ask (the followers of) Our messengers whom We sent before you: did We appoint any gods to be served other than the beneficent"
  43,46,"And We have certainly sent Moses with Our signs to Pharaoh and his assembly, then he said: I am a messenger from the Master of Human kind"
  43,47,"But when he brought them Our miracles, they laughed at it"